We recommend hosting solutions through our green hosting partners, OVHcloud or Scaleway, both located in France and utilizing 100% renewable energy. Their Power Usage Effectiveness (PUE) ratings are 1.3 and 1.28 respectively, indicating efficient energy use. Both partners are ISO14001 certified, ensuring adherence to environmental management standards.

To reduce our digital footprint, we will implement several digital sobriety practices. These include model quantization techniques like INT8/INT4, which can reduce GPU energy consumption by approximately 40%. We also plan to utilize auto-scaling to minimize resource usage outside business hours and implement query result caching to reduce recomputations by an estimated 20%. Furthermore, our green IT hardware procurement policy ensures that equipment has a minimum lifecycle of 5 years.

In terms of e-waste management, we partner with Ecologic in France for certified WEEE recycling, ensuring responsible disposal of electronic waste. Our carbon reporting capability, aligned with GRI Standards (albeit partially), allows us to monitor and report our carbon footprint effectively.

Socially, we are committed to maintaining a high gender equality index of 88 and ensuring accessibility standards such as WCAG 2.1 AA and RGAA 4.1. We also prioritize local subcontracting and provide an average of 42 training hours per employee per year.

Our AI ethics charter, which includes principles like mandatory human oversight for AI recommendations, quarterly bias testing to prevent discriminatory outputs, transparency of data sources, and the right to contest AI-generated suggestions, will guide the development and deployment of AI solutions. Regular quarterly bias audits and a whistleblowing policy further ensure accountability and fairness in our AI practices.

However, we are aware of potential CSR tensions that may arise, such as balancing high availability with energy consumption, the challenge of ensuring on-premise servers use green energy, and optimizing model size for performance while minimizing energy usage. For these, we propose resolutions like using low-power standby modes, recommending clients to subscribe to renewable energy Guarantee of Origin certificates, and preferring quantised mid-size models with fine-tuning over larger, unoptimised ones.

By implementing these measures and being mindful of the known sustainability trade-offs, we believe we can contribute significantly to reducing the environmental footprint of the city of Belval's project while upholding strong social commitments and ethical AI practices.
