The City of Belval has initiated a call for tenders for the implementation of an artificial intelligence (AI) solution to assist municipal agents in their daily missions, enhancing efficiency and service quality. Our consortium proposes a comprehensive AI-powered assistance tool designed to meet the city's specific needs, ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements, particularly GDPR, and aligning with sustainable development goals. Leveraging our expertise in API integration, cloud hosting on EU-based infrastructure, AI model development, and green IT practices, we aim to deliver a high-performance, secure, and environmentally friendly solution.

# 2. Understanding of Requirements
We have thoroughly reviewed the call for tenders and understand the need for an intelligent assistance tool that can facilitate access to information, improve the quality of answers, and reduce processing times for municipal agents. The solution must integrate with existing systems, ensure high availability and performance, and comply with GDPR and other regulatory requirements. Additionally, there is a strong emphasis on sovereignty, security, innovation, and environmental sustainability.

# 3. Proposed Solution
### Technical Domain
Our proposed architecture leverages API gateways like Kong, message brokers like Apache Kafka, and containerization using Kubernetes on Outscale's SecNumCloud-certified infrastructure. This ensures EU-only hosting, high performance (with a response time of less than 2 seconds), and availability exceeding 99.9%. Integration with existing systems such as EDM, civil status software, and town planning tools will be facilitated through API interfaces.

### Legal Domain
We address legal risks by ensuring GDPR compliance through EU-only hosting, preventing unauthorized data transfers, encrypting sensitive data, and providing explainability in AI recommendations. Contractual clauses will be included to address GDPR compliance, explicability, and intellectual property rights, mitigating vendor lock-in risks.

### Financial Domain
Our financial proposal is based on a maximum contract value of 3 million euros over 4 years, with an annual cost of exploitation that remains within the municipal budget capacity. We aim to optimize costs through a phased approach, prioritizing essential services and potentially phasing in less critical components based on budget constraints.

### AI Innovation Domain
Our Large Language Model (LLM) stack, particularly the Mistral 7B Instruct model, will be fine-tuned for French-language tasks and integrated with Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) capabilities to provide accurate and context-specific responses. Innovations such as knowledge graphs for procedural reasoning and multi-agent collaboration frameworks will enhance the tool's effectiveness.

### Sustainability Domain
To support the City of Belval's sustainable development policy, we propose leveraging green hosting partners like OVHcloud or Scaleway, implementing digital sobriety practices (including model quantization and auto-scaling), and ensuring responsible e-waste management. Our approach aims to minimize energy consumption while maintaining performance, aligning with GRI Standards for carbon reporting.

# 4. Compliance & Certifications
Our solution will comply with all regulatory requirements, including GDPR, with specific measures such as EU-only hosting, encryption of sensitive data, and explicability in AI recommendations. We also ensure compliance with technical constraints like performance (response time < 2 seconds) and availability (>99.9%).

# 5. Budget Overview
The total contract value is estimated at 3 million euros over a duration of 4 years. Our approach to cost optimization includes a phased implementation, prioritization of services based on budget capacity, and exploration of efficiencies through process optimization and strategic partnerships.

# 6. Conclusion
Our consortium's proposal for the City of Belval's AI-powered assistance tool is built on a deep understanding of the city's needs, combining technical expertise, legal compliance, financial responsibility, innovative AI solutions, and a commitment to sustainability. We believe our comprehensive approach will not only meet but exceed the expectations outlined in the call for tenders, contributing to the efficiency, quality of service, and environmental goals of the City of Belval.
